By Offering (Hardware, Software, and Services)

- Mainframes are primarily categorized into hardware, software, and services, with hardware encompassing the physical components and infrastructure required for computing tasks, software covering the operating systems and applications that run on mainframes, and services including maintenance, support, and consultancy for optimizing mainframe performance and operations.

Application (Census Industry, Consumer Statics, ERP and Transaction)

- Mainframes find applications in various industries such as census industry for processing large volumes of data efficiently, consumer statistics for data analytics and trend analysis, enterprise resource planning (ERP) systems for seamless integration and management of business processes, and transactional systems for handling high-volume, secure transactions.

Organization Size (Large Enterprises and Small and Medium-Sized Enterprises)

- The mainframe market caters to organizations of different sizes, including large enterprises requiring robust computing capabilities, scalability, and reliability to support complex operations, as well as small and medium-sized enterprises seeking cost-effective mainframe solutions tailored to their specific business needs and growth aspirations.

